text: Rudolph is an unincorporated community in Brown County, in the U.S. state of South Dakota. ==History== Rudolph was laid out in 1881. It was named for H. Rudolph McCullough, a railroad official. A post office called Rudolph was established in 1883, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1908. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Brown County, South Dakota Category:Unincorporated communities in South Dakota
title: Rudolph, South Dakota
